Cassandra, which can be found at https://cassandra.apache.org/_/index.html is an open-source "No SQL" database created to handle massive data. 
The data model Cassandra is columns "No SQL" which utilises key-store where data is stored in sets of rows organized into tables. This is grouped
by columns ina "column-family" technique. 
The hosting model is a client/server where many clients are connected to a common server. 
Cassandra can be accessed from Java by using the Java Database Connectivity (JDBC) API or through python based on the Cassandra Query Language (CQL)
